<br>
Any way, at 25 I started taking a Dark Bone Skeleton in my spawn cycle because they were good EP and decent treasure.  After I got the pieces, I then started killing DBS for ep.  They were 4 of them and all of them can be single pulled.  The only problem was if the wandering orge guard wander by just after you started attacking one.   I stayed there until I was 32.  Not once did any of the focus pieces drop.  This was about May of 2002.  .  <br>
<br>
I sucspect the loot tables for the DBS got linked to the magicians tables and probably (have been) /(will be) fixed.  If you are high level and hunting for the pieces, it probably won't hurt to try them, but I don't think they will drop them for long.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kiediscuchulainn>Kiedis CuChulainn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 2:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1042.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: buy em</span><hr size=1> Just last night I killed Rathyl and Rathly Reincarnate and the Reincarnate dropped A Stein and a Traveler's Pack.<br>
